author: IGN
description:
Don't miss the Vibrant Visuals Reveal Trailer for Minecraft, a creation adventure game developed by Mojang. author: IGN
description:
Look at this Minecraft gameplay comparison, featuring the new Minecraft update, Minecraft Vibrant Visuals, vs. the current version of the game. Minecraft Vibrant Visuals is an upcoming upgrade to Minecraft: Bedrock Edition which is adding graphical enhancements such as volumetric fog, directional lighting, and more. Mojang Studios describe this Minecraft upgrade as their 'developer's vision' for what Minecraft will look like going forward, with not just the Bedrock Edition, but also, the Minecraft Java Edition sometime in the future as well. Get a look at this Minecraft graphics comparison and let us know what you think in the comments!

#Minecraft #Gaming #Games
title: Minecraft Graphics Update Comparison (Vibrant Visuals)

#GodOfWar #Kratos #Gaming

author: IGN
description:
Thanks to his slow climbing and reliance on strength over stealth, Yasuke turns Assassin's Creed Shadows into a very different kind of game. With a renewed focus on the ideas the Assassin's Creed game series was originally built on, AC Shadows is the most satisfying Assassin’s Creed has felt in years. You can fluidly move from ground to castle rooftop thanks to the best parkour system since Unity, and a grappling hook only makes the journey to a great vantage point even speedier. Perched on a tightrope high above the enemy, you’re only a drop away from scoring the perfect kill… provided you’re playing as Naoe, that is. Take control of Yasuke, Assassin's Creed Shadows’ second protagonist, and it’s a whole different game.

#AssassinsCreedShadows #AssassinsCreed #Gaming
title: Playing as Yasuke in AC Shadows Doesn't Feel Like Assassin's Creed, He’s Something New

author: IGN
description:
Xenoblade Chronicles X: Definitive Edition is out now, and it’s one of the most ambitious open-world RPGs you’ll ever play. Join Logan Plant and IGN reviewer George Yang as they dive into what makes this game so special. From its massive, alien world to its deep customization and Skell mechs, Xenoblade Chronicles X offers an unforgettable adventure.
George breaks down the changes from the original, why this Definitive Edition is worth your time, and where newcomers should start in the Xenoblade series. Whether you’re a longtime fan or new to the franchise, this is a must-watch for RPG lovers.
title: Why Xenoblade Chronicles X Is an Amazing RPG - NVC Clips

author: IGN
description: When a trailer is released for a movie or a show, that usually means it’s coming out soon, but video games are another story, sometimes getting trailers years before they’re released. In some cases, though, they get cancelled after a trailer has already been made public. So, we pulled together some trailers for games that never came out, whether due to cancellation, studio closure, a massive rebranding, or because they’re still supposedly in development. From infamous unreleased games like Blizzard’s Starcraft Ghost and Ubisoft’s Beyond Good & Evil 2, to games that didn’t resemble their original trailers at all, like Duke Nukem Forever or Bethesda’s original Prey 2, which had nothing to do with the eventual Prey sequel developed by Arkane Austin. We delve into some of the many licensed games that got teased prior to cancellation, like Marvel Chaos, THQ’s Avengers game, Star Wars 1313 and Indiana Jones and the Staff of Kings. While we did eventually get a few of the games on this list
title: 15 Awesome Trailers For Games That Never Came Out
